race.comment: GALLANT STAR (7) looks ready to explode first-up in the $2 Million Kosciuszko. Trialled superbly twice leading in and lands the dream draw to stalk the hot early tempo. If he produces his best turn of foot fresh, he'll take some stopping. CLEAR THINKING (11) returns with three trials under her belt, the latest a beauty with blinkers on, which she wears for the first time here. Gets in light, and with an honest tempo she'll be charging home. A huge threat. FRONT PAGE (1), the two-time Kosciuszko king is back again and always commands respect. Will go forward and take catching, though the weight could bite late. BANDI'S BOY (2) brings flashes of brilliance and Purton's booking catches the eye. COMPELLING TRUTH (3) comes off the G2 Shorts. Wasn't effective there but prior form stacks right up. Don't dismiss.
